What is the surface area of a triangular prism with a base that is an
equilateral triangle with a side length of 4.2cm and a height of 6cm, and with
the prism's height equal to 1.8cm?

Base area............
B = bh/2
B = (4.2)(6)(0.5)
B = 12.6

Lateral area.........
L = ph
L = 3(4.2)(1.8)
L = 22.68

Surface area.........
S = L + 2B
S = 22.68 + 2(12.6)
S = 22.68 + 25.2
S = 47.88

