If the length, width, and height of the rectangular prism in the figure above
were doubled, what would be the surface area of the prism?

New dimensions........................
l = 2(8) = 16
w = 2(2) = 4
h = 2(3) = 6

Surface area..........................
S = 2wh + 2lh + 2lw
S = 2(4 * 6) + 2(16 * 6) + 2(16 * 4)
S = 2(24) + 2(96) + 2(64)
S = 48 + 192 + 128
S = 368

Surface area (alt)....................
S = ph + 2B
S = (2l + 2w)(h) + 2lw
S = (2(16) + 2(4))(6) + 2(16 * 4)
S = (32 + 8)(6) + 2(64)
S = (40)(6) + 128
S = 240 + 128
S = 368

